def my_func(input1: str) -> str:
    if not input1 or len(input1) < 2:
        return input1

    # Calculate a unique index based on the ASCII value of the first character
    unique_index = ord(input1[0]) % len(input1)

    # Calculate a second unique index based on the ASCII value of the last character
    unique_index_second = ord(input1[-1]) % len(input1)

    # Select two characters using the calculated indices as a slice
    return input1[min(unique_index, unique_index_second):max(unique_index, unique_index_second)+1]
